The course introduces different approaches, concepts, processes, and supporting factors of co-creation. An important part of the course is gaining practical experience as an observer or participant in a co-creation process. Some parts of the course are designed co-creatively.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to get familiar with co-creation and networking to know the possibilities of co-creative approaches and to be able to apply them.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  * Recognizes and can use the basic concepts of co-creation and networking * Orients in different co-creative methodologies, knows their main advantages and disadvantages and is able to choose them when planning a co-creational process * Knows the stages of the co-creation process * Is aware of factors that enable and support co-creation and can apply them consciously * Has gained experience in participating in or observing co-creation process
